1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ Database Connection Concept

### Example Class

```python
class Product:
    id
    name
    description
    price
    quantity
```

### Mapping Concept

| Python Object | Database |
| ------------- | -------- |
| Class         | Table    |
| Attributes    | Columns  |
| Object        | Row      |


1ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£ ORM â€“ Object Relational Mapping

### What is ORM?

* Converts **Python objects â†” Database rows**
* No need to write raw SQL

Example:

```python
Product(
    id=1,
    name="phone",
    price=20000,
    description="Vivo Y7",
    qty=7
)
```

â¡ Automatically stored as a database row


1ï¸âƒ£3ï¸âƒ£ SQLAlchemy (Why We Use It)

### Problems Without ORM:

âŒ Manual table creation
âŒ Manual SQL queries
âŒ Error-prone
âŒ Hard to maintain

### SQLAlchemy Solves:

âœ” Auto table creation
âœ” Object-based queries
âœ” Database independent
âœ” Clean & scalable


1ï¸âƒ£4ï¸âƒ£ Database Driver

